<plot>PLAY TIME explores overcoming adversity through a non-traditional lens. Mark, a single father in his early forties- struggles to cope with some of the harsh realities of his life. One afternoon, he decides to get away from it all at a local community park. A homeless man greets Mark upon arrival, selling prophetic poetry for a dollar. His insights launch Mark into a journey of surprises and self-discovery.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?435116</url></doc>
